==English==
===Etymology===
[[poly-]] + [[diabolo|(di)abolo]], from the resemblance of a diabolo in cross-section to two right isosceles triangles joined at the vertices of their right angles

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''polyabolo''' (''plural'' '''polyabolos''' ''or'' '''polyaboloes'''; ''by analogy with'' '''diabolo''', '''polyabolos''' ''would be the correct plural, but'' '''polyaboloes''' ''is just as commonly seen, if not more so'')

#{{geometry}} A [[polyform]] made by joining [[right]] [[isosceles]] [[triangle]]s edge to edge in various [[arrangement]]s.

